Probabilistic Methods, Neural Networks

The paper belongs to the sub-category of Probabilistic Methods because it discusses the use of Bayesian networks to model data and make predictions. The authors also mention the use of Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) methods for inference.

The paper also belongs to the sub-category of Neural Networks because it discusses the use of deep learning models for data exploration. The authors mention the use of autoencoders and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction and dimensionality reduction. They also discuss the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for time series analysis.
